{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff between summary-persistence logic and stored per-dimension findings for the same round. A unit test of one function can miss query/join/filter mismatches across modules. Higher levels were considered and rejected: behavior text is about stored verdict consistency, not real OS/network/subprocess (so not System), not model output quality (so not Agentic), and not multiple agentic steps (so not Workflow).","test_description":"Wire summary save service + findings repository (test DB/fixtures). Seed same-round findings with at least one FAIL, attempt to persist PASS summary, assert save is rejected and error references conflicting dimension verdicts.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure appears when gate computation and storage layer disagree with hand-written summary text; that is cross-module data-source selection. Unit tests can miss wiring errors where gate reads summary field instead of findings table. Rejected higher levels: behavior text specifies stored findings vs summary text, with no real OS/network requirement, no dependence on LLM judgment, and no multi-agent sequence.","test_description":"Compose gate with real repository adapter (local test DB). Store findings containing FAIL plus summary text claiming all PASS. Run gate computation and assert verdict is FAIL/block based on findings, proving summary text is ignored as sole source.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is policy enforcement across input validation + persistence/audit logging modules. Unit-only checks can miss missing audit writes or flag propagation bugs. Rejected higher levels: behavior does not require real OS/network/subprocess; it does not depend on AI output quality; it is not a multi-agent chain.","test_description":"Call summary finalization path without override flag and assert manual override is rejected. Repeat with override flag and assert success only with an audit warning record persisted (including actor/round/reason metadata).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.73,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the gate requires a review round identifier produced after the latest fix commit before PASS can be finalized.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is temporal/state handoff across commit-tracking and review-round metadata modules. A unit test can miss stale-ID acceptance caused by repository/query wiring. Rejected higher levels: text requires ordering by commit/round IDs, not real subprocess git behavior; no dependence on LLM output quality; single gate rule, not multi-agent sequence.","test_description":"Seed latest fix commit SHA/time and two review rounds (one before, one after fix). Attempt PASS with pre-fix round ID and assert block; attempt with post-fix round ID and assert eligible.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"In the live review loop, PASS cannot finalize unless a fresh review-agent round runs on the updated diff.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary risk is orchestration/state: diff update must trigger/require a new round before finalization. This can be caught with integrated loop state machine + round-run registry. Agentic was considered but rejected because behavior text checks execution precondition ('fresh round runs on updated diff'), not correctness of model judgment content. System rejected: no required real OS/network behavior stated.","test_description":"Run live-loop orchestration with updated diff marker. Attempt final PASS before launching new round and assert block. Execute one new round event tied to updated diff, then assert finalization can proceed only after that fresh-round state is recorded.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.13,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings in stored results, the outcome is escalation rather than PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Rule depends on combining round-budget state and stored MUST-FIX findings; this is cross-module policy evaluation. Unit tests can miss integration bugs where one state source is ignored. Rejected higher levels: behavior text is stored-results policy, not real OS/network/subprocess, not model-output-quality dependent, and not explicitly multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Seed stored findings with unresolved MUST-FIX and set round counter to exhausted. Run decision engine and assert outcome is escalation and PASS is blocked.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"In a live multi-round review workflow, exhausted rounds with unresolved MUST-FIX findings still block PASS and emit escalation.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior explicitly targets a live multi-round workflow with sequencing across rounds; failure emerges from end-to-end state carryover through multiple review stages, not a single module boundary. Rejected lower levels: Integration can miss sequence/order bugs across rounds; Agentic alone is insufficient because this requires multiple staged decisions/events in sequence ('live multi-round review workflow', 'exhausted rounds').","test_description":"Execute an end-to-end multi-round run: rounds 1..N produce/retain unresolved MUST-FIX, consume full round budget, then attempt finalization. Assert PASS remains blocked and escalation event is emitted with linkage to unresolved findings and exhausted-round state.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.65}}]}
